  "Testing Connection": "",
  "The Custom Menu Links plugin allows administrators to add external links to the navigation menu. When enabled, a 'Links' menu appears in the sidebar containing all configured links.": "",
  "The External Backup plugin allows you to automatically backup your ChurchCRM database to WebDAV-compatible cloud storage services. This includes popular services like Nextcloud, ownCloud, or any server supporting WebDAV protocol.": "",
  "The default OpenLP port is 4316. Your server URL will typically be: http://192.168.x.x:4316 where 192.168.x.x is the IP address of the computer running OpenLP. You can find this in OpenLP under Tools → Open Service Manager.": "",
  "The month that starts your organization's fiscal year": "",
  "This plugin is currently used for Kiosk Check-in Notifications. When a child is checked into a Sunday School class via the kiosk system, an SMS can be sent to notify parents or guardians.": "",
  "This plugin is currently used for Kiosk Check-in Notifications. When a child is checked into a Sunday School class via the kiosk system, an alert can be sent to the OpenLP projector display to notify parents or volunteers.": "",
  "This plugin transmits email addresses to MailChimp servers. Ensure you have appropriate consent from your members before syncing their information to third-party services like MailChimp.": "",
  "To add a new link:\n1. Go to the Links menu in the sidebar and click 'Manage Links'\n2. Enter a display name (2-50 characters)\n3. Enter the full URL (must start with http:// or https://)\n4. Click 'Add Link'\n\nThe link will immediately appear in the Links menu.": "",
  "To configure external backups:\n1. Go to Admin > Plugins and find 'External Backup (WebDAV)'\n2. Click the settings icon to expand the configuration panel\n3. Enter your WebDAV endpoint URL (e.g., https://cloud.example.com/remote.php/dav/files/username/backups/)\n4. Enter your username and password\n5. Optionally set an auto-backup interval in hours\n6. Save your settings": "",
  "To use MailChimp Integration, you need a MailChimp account and an API key.\n\n1. Log in to your MailChimp account\n2. Go to Account > Extras > API Keys\n3. Create a new API key or copy an existing one\n4. Enter the API key in the plugin settings": "",
